caption:
Meet Merry!! This beautiful, intelligent girl is AARF's #wcw!  She loves to ride in the car and run on the beach!! She loves tennis balls and tug-o-war.  Merry and the rest of her siblings play a fun game of hide and seek or chase, it's very cute! She is very affectionate and just loves to cuddle!  Merry will need a loving hand. She is a loving, intelligent animal who needs a lot of stimulus. Merry will do well in a house with older children and at least 1 other dog. Merry is kennel trained for 4-5 hour stretches, and she sleeps through the night - averaging 6 -7 hours.  Merry has storm and noise anxiety and will destroy a crate in a storm or with fireworks. Merry is housebroken, although we use a doggy door so she has full access to house and yard.

Merry is a #boxer #shepherd #sharpei mix that is about 7.5 years old and 75 lbs.

Because of #covid19 we are not doing adoption events. We are still accepting online applications at aarfhouston.org, and will find a time for a meet and greet. Thank you for considering a #rescue!

caption:
You may not feel Fear at all, but put you in a room with just 10 people that are terrified, then suddenly you become terrified.

The survival rate of this virus is actually very high. Although you won't find that statistic anywhere because I actually tried looking it up. All I find is death rates between.... If you have health issues, then like always, take extra care of yourself. As you always should.

If you are prone to picking up every cold, or flu bug around, then boost your immune system by getting a healthy stomach. (immune system is in the stomach)

Don't let the fear get you, because you know why? Fear puts your body in the Fight and Flight mode which plummets the immune system faster than anything you could do. 
Stay out of fear for many reasons.
The number one reason is that you cannot change the situation. Your fear is not helping anyone. Fear is the future, fear is a probable.
If you cannot get out of fear then turn to your faith. Whatever it takes before it takes you down.

caption:
Privilege has been on my mind lately, yaâ€™ll. ğŸ˜£Systematic inequalities have always been present in our society but this pandemic has really thrust them into the spotlight. Although Covid-19 has been touted as an â€œequal-opportunity killer,â€ in that it can and will infect anyone, in practice this is just not the case. The most vulnerable in our society will be more adversely affected due to a lack of privilege, wealth and resources. Unfortunately, socioeconomic status and race are closely intertwined in the U.S., which means that coronavirus will disproportionately affect racial minority groups. Recent stats support this too, as black Americans make up a disproportionate number of U.S. covid-19 deaths thus far. 
Many individuals are having to make the impossible choice between staying at home and not being able to pay bills, or to go to work and risk contracting covid-19. Please keep in mind that it is a privilege to:

Have shelter

Be safe at home, without threat of domestic violence or abuse 
Live in a home that is not overcrowded

Afford food, delivery/take-out

Stockpile food and supplies

Work from home

Access adequate healthcare

Yes, we are bored and restless, and frankly may even feel like we're losing our damn minds. ğŸ¤¯ But, if you are privileged like me, let's practice gratitude for the privileges we have, and show compassion to those who are forced to go to work, continue to use public transportation or are struggling to afford rent or food. Hereâ€™s the funny thing about going through the motions: when the motions stop, and the going through them is then forced to stop, it creates space, time, and opportunity to think about your own life:â£
â£
Whatâ€™s working really well?â£
What isnâ€™t?â£
Why do we do the things we do?â£
Why donâ€™t we do the things we want to do...or at least the things we say we want to?â£
What does it all mean?â£
â£
Itâ€™s very easy to go through the motions. Startlingly easy, actually. So easy that we can lose sight of our â€œwhyâ€ and just keep repeating patterns... not because weâ€™re particularly passionate about them, but because itâ€™s what weâ€™ve always done. â£
â£
Our patterns have been disrupted. There has been a collective record scratchy noise that has everyone, in their own unique way, taking a closer look at their own life in a new way, and starting to ask those questions. â£
â£
This is a collective wake up call, and weâ€™re experiencing it en masse, but in a hyper individualized way. â£
â£
This life is precious. Too precious to sleepwalk through the rest of it. â£
â£
If youâ€™re starting to wake up and wonder where you are, how you got here, and if this really is all there is, message me. Letâ€™s chat about how to move forward from here. â£
â£
What an incredible opportunity it is to wake up from your own life.

I feel extremely lucky that home doubled as my office even before Covid-19 sent us all into lockdown. 
But I know that for many, the way you do business has changed immeasurably and it may not be the same for some time to come. 
For some, the health and safety of staff, clients and yourselves will mean the lockdown will continue in some form or other. 
For others, being forced to stop, or at least slow down, for four (plus? ğŸ™…ğŸ½â€â™€ï¸ğŸ¤ğŸ½) weeks might have had you reconsidering the way you would like to run your business in future in order to maintain some form of a positive work-life balance. 
I've certainly missed the face to face contact that comes with many business interactions throughout the past few weeks, but there's no question that we have some amazing tools and technologies at our fingertips that allow many of us to work efficiently from right here in our homes. Can you imagine if this lockdown had have been even just 10 years ago?! Maybe you'd like to continue using some of those tools to save you time even beyond this lockdown. But then, maybe you don't, and that's fine too. 
One thing that remains important either way is communication. Talk to your clients now about how they can reach you going forward and how you are likely to be running your business in the coming weeks and months.

caption:
Mental health includes physical movement! Dance/movement therapy (DMT) is defined by the American Dance Therapy Association (ADTA) as the psychotherapeutic use of movement to promote emotional, social, cognitive, and physical integration of the individual, for the purpose of improving health and well-being. Movement releases our feel-good neurotransmitters just like dopamine and will help reduce stress, anxiety and depression. â 
â 
When we look at athletes, many folks wonder how athletes remain so committed, how they are seemingly addicted to their craft. It's because releasing, by way of movement, fuels us and makes us FEEL GOOD. â 
â 
With that being said, I'm excited to announce this special workshop in collaboration with choreographer & movement coach, @officialjenzi! I will open with insight on the benefits of movement, Jenzi will then lead us in a fun and easy dance routine, and then I will close with a meditation to prep us for an enjoyable weekend to follow. â 
â 
No matter your age, physical ability, coordination, this is for you! Join us and just have FUN! â 
â 
Reserve your spot now!â

caption:
Do you have a pile of extra flat sheets that you're not using & don't know what to do with?â €
â €
Have you considered donating them to be made into "scrub bags" for our frontline care workers?â €
â €
There are many groups of people who are creating cloth drawstring bags for our healthcare workers to transport their used scrubs home & throw right into the wash as they try to do their best not to spread any germs they may have come in contact with.â €
â €
We have been sending pillowcases and sheets across Alberta to some of these groups so that they can be made into these useful tools for our doctors, nurses & other healthcare workers. We are so grateful for all that they do and sacrifice for our health & safety and are trying to do whatever we can to support them.â €
â €
So, if you have extra sheets, pillowcases or other fabric that you no longer need, this is a fantastic way to put them to good use & offer a little assistance during this crazy time.â €
â €
A quick google search will bring up lots of groups looking for fabric donations in your area & you can even find patterns if you're looking to make some yourself. We're all in this together and we cannot express how grateful we are for our frontline workers and all that they're doing for us.

If you had a big wedding planned with all of your favorite people celebrating, thatâ€™s wonderful. And I hope that you are able to reschedule that party and enjoy it to the fullest!

If youâ€™ve chosen to get married on your original date with a few other people, I want to encourage you IT CAN BE SO GOOD. And so sweet and intimate.

Iâ€™m working on one more resource for those of you in this situation, but I want to encourage you - that as you grieve the loss of what your wedding day was supposed to look like, make a big deal of the good that remains.

Everything looks different right now because of COVID; but I want you to be able to fight fiercely and hold onto the wonder of the day that you get married. The freedom of a day where the two of you can commit to each other, walk down memory lane, smile over everything that youâ€™ve made it through and over everything youâ€™re going to make it through together.

Make the day you get married about that, and youâ€™ll have good feelings when you look back on that day. Bittersweet - but good. And thatâ€™s what I want for you.

caption:
Ever have one of those moments where you realize how fortunate you are?

I have had my present job for over a year. I have hated it for almost as long as I have had it. Donâ€™t get me wrong, I was always grateful I had a job, but I am not able to use most of the skills and experience I have acquired. I am not challenged in my present position, which frustrates me. 
During this #pandemic, Iâ€™ve realized that my job is a blessing in disguise. Iâ€™ve lamented how bored I am, and that Iâ€™m underpaid for my skills & experience. However, I have a job that isnâ€™t affected by the economic downturn as a result of #corona #virus. Not only that, but my job adapted to the #crisis by making it possible to work from home. Additionally, the benefits like the Employee Assistance Program (EAP) and health insurance, allow me to provide the care that my son needs. 
Due to #Covid19, my ex & I have altered our time sharing arrangement to minimize our time in public for exchanges. As a result, The Kid has been a little anxious. Heâ€™s ready for things to go back to normal.

Yesterday, I called the EAP number to get him some free counseling sessions to deal with his anxiety during this time. The person I spoke with screens peopleâ€™s requests to determine if authorization should be given for counseling sessions. After she listened to my concerns and approved my request, she asked, â€œhow are you doing?â€ I told her I was anxious trying to balance working from home, helping my son with his distance learning, while being unable to â€œresetâ€ myself by going for a hike on the weekends. I explained that I had poured myself into learning to paint as a way to manage my stress. 
Iâ€™ve been finding photos on Insta that interest me and trying to paint them as I learn new techniques. The photo I used for this painting is by @numbskull10415. My sun is a little jacked, but itâ€™s still a #workinprogress. So, how are you? What are you doing during the #coronavirus #quarantine to stay sane? #stayathome during #pandemic2020 #stopthespread of #cvid19 #covid

caption:
Old photo: different caption. In which I share moments of reality and how my Lord uses these moments to teach me about forgiveness and grace.
â€¢
Yesterday we went back to how it all started a month ago â€œyou are the worse teacher, I like you more as a mother.â€ My son said because he didnâ€™t want to listen to instruction of writing â€˜a catâ€™ with space. â€œAnd you are the worse student.â€ Oh dear, I went too far but I was having a hard time at beginning of homeschooling week 4. By snack time I wanted both children out of the house for PE in the garden. On his way to the garden he says â€œyou are the best mother ever.â€ I fumed and say â€œjust go!â€
â€¢
By 3pm I was by the sink, with my daughter throwing her journal on the toy storage, a Ghanaian sign of defiance that I canâ€™t stand. After she had forgotten her behaviour about five minutes later, she came and asked me â€œare you okay? Are you cross?â€ â€œNo really, Iâ€™m sad. Iâ€™m just praying for you.â€ I said but nothing really came out of it. She went back to her play and I went to my dishes. It was then that I felt the Lord talking to me. He held my heart and said â€œthe journey with me is a daily surrendering. Forgive.â€ It was hard because I can be stubborn but with the mighty knowledge that Christ lives in me and forgives me 77x7 I surrendered and called my daughter for a hug. It felt good and I remembered how Jesus encourages to take our cross and follow Him daily. Having the Holy Spirit in us doesnâ€™t mean we are perfect but it means that the perfect One lives in us so He will always remind us of the good action to take.
â€¢
Suddenly what felt like a tempestuous day turned into a calm late afternoon, listening to Bible verses and just being gracious to one another. My son cuddling me and me saying sorry for the hard morning. All glory to a wonderful peace maker, my Saviour. He is resurrected and He with me teaching me His holy ways daily.
â€¢
Iâ€™m called to share the good, the bad and the ugly. As much as I donâ€™t feel comfortable with it, I want to be obedient to the calling. Today itâ€™s all calmed, doing unschooling again but most importantly we started with a family prayer.

W.B. YEATS

To a Child Dancing in the Wind

I

DANCE there upon the shore; 
What need have you to care 
For wind or waterâ€™s roar? 
And tumble out your hair 
That the salt drops have wet;  5
Being young you have not known 
The foolâ€™s triumph, nor yet 
Love lost as soon as won, 
Nor the best labourer dead 
And all the sheaves to bind.  10
What need have you to dread 
The monstrous crying of wind? 
II

Has no one said those daring 
Kind eyes should be more learnâ€™d? 
Or warned you how despairing  15
The moths are when they are burned, 
I could have warned you, but you are young, 
So we speak a different tongue. 
O you will take whateverâ€™s offered 
And dream that all the worldâ€™s a friend,  20
Suffer as your mother suffered, 
Be as broken in the end. 
But I am old and you are young, 
And I speak a barbarous tongue.

I wouldnâ€™t really call it a hobby, but Iâ€™ve been observing face masks lately and have even been experiencing some envy at the cute and creative ones! â€¢
Today was my first time wearing â€œthe mask.â€ And I didnâ€™t even know how to really do it. Did it go over my nose, or not?
â€¢
When it was over my nose, I couldnâ€™t really breathe well and my glasses fogged up when I spoke. So I cheated sometimes, I think.
â€¢
I bought this mask over five years ago for working in my large garden in Northwestern Pennsylvania.
â€¢
It was plain, blue, and definitely on the boring side.
â€¢
A lady in the parking lot today had on a black stylish mask and was obviously a pro at this. And the lady in a waiting area had on a red Micky Mouse mask. â€¢

Since I was a kid I have been going to Niagara Falls and now I take my kids a few times a year.  I have been in -20 degree temps when the falls were frozen, hot sunny weather, rainy fall and cool spring days. In all my years of going the street has NEVER been empty!

I knew with the COVID19 pandemic that it was going to be empty but I needed to see and capture it for myself. I know, I know I'm suppose to stay home but yesterday I needed out of the house, even if it was only to drive the van 2 hours to capture the emptiness and drive home.  I needed to capture these images so I could show my kids and even my grandkids when I'm older. 
Those streets are always packed with cars, packed with screaming kids, full of laughter and excitement seeing all the cool stores and shops down Clifton Hill. Viewing the falls from the sidewalk is almost impossible on a good day, let alone having a clear view from the car. It was almost surreal seeing it like that.  This is a moment in history and I want to capture it, safely of course, maintaining social distance and not risking my health or the health of others.

Its a crazy world we are living in right now and we really don't know when things will return to "normal" or if they ever will be "normal" again.  May this virus pass quickly and these streets be full of life again <3

Stay safe and feel free to share <3

caption:
We're not going to lie - the last few weeks haven't been easy. We operate at the intersection of education and the arts, and both of those industries have been sent reeling in the face of this pandemic.

However, there have been some incredibly bright spots in the midst of this, and that's what this post is about. ğŸ’œ

Our students have thrown themselves into their new learning styles with gusto and enthusiasm. We are in awe of their resilience, determination and desire to keep moving toward their goals. 
Our Brio parents have offered such incredible words of encouragement and genuine thanks as we have worked to pivot into virtual learning - we hope they know how much we appreciate them. 
And our incredible faculty have really brought everything to the table for our students. They've recorded HUNDREDS of hours of content (with new content added weekly), they've re-designed curriculum, created new learning plans to support virtual learning, and they're out there, running virtual classes like pros! We are so grateful for them.

In many ways - big and small - we've been able to look around in the midst of this chaos and be so grateful for the many, many reasons we have to keep going and keep innovating. 
And if you've ever wondered what the parent-end of a live class looks like, check out this video! Miss Jenna ran our first live training choir rehearsal today, to the delight of her students. Here's Elijah, age 5, singing his heart out with 'His Jenna'. We hope this makes you smile, like it made us smile. ğŸ˜

Brio parents, if you catch a photo or video of your student doing virtual class, send it out way! We know you're capturing amazing, era-defining photos and videos at home, and we'd love it if you'd share them with us.

caption:
"Just snap out of it! What do you have to be stressed about?" Well... wouldn't it be nice if that was that easy?
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
I've listed a few obvious and a few "not-so-obvious" ways to switch your body from "fight or flight" (or sympathetic nervous system) to "rest and digest" (parasympathetic) below. Some require longer explanations than I can list here, so I will add some inspiration to my stories!
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
Our brain has evolved and evolved over time in order to keep us safe, so "snapping out of it" during a moment of high-stress or panic involves lots of practice.
The obvious:
âœ”ï¸ Exercise (even 5 mins of dancing like my sons here in the rain or jumping jacks)
âœ”ï¸ Talking to yourself (quietly or out loud!) and saying something like: "I am safe."
âœ”ï¸ Breathing: try breathing in through your nose for 5, holding for 5, then exhaling through your nose for 7. Or, you can try 4x4x4x4 (adding in a step of waiting to inhale again for 4)
âœ”ï¸ Phone-a-friend: bonus point if they make you laugh ğŸ˜‰
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
The not-so-obvious:
âœ”ï¸ Shaking (stand up, shake your shoulders, your hands, wrists, hips, ankles, feet)
âœ”ï¸ Tapping (EFT or "Emotional Freedom Technique")
âœ”ï¸ Humming (think chanting like a monk- humming stimulates your vagus nerve)
âœ”ï¸ Mindfulness (according to @_drsoph, this is NOT about "clearing your mind"- it's actually about noticing your thoughts and bringing yourself back to the present moment, over and over.)
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
What stress/anxiety/panic reducing techniques work for you?

I am a nurse, not a martyr! This illustrates how me and so many of my colleagues feel right now...nurses, physicians, radiology technologists, respiratory therapists and everyone on the frontline.

You applaud us! But will you stay at home? Will you be in favor of not reopening the economy too soon?

Let me tell you. Healthcare is business first and your well being last! The PPE deficit is the biggest letdown in a work culture that already does little about addressing unsafe nurse to patient ratios and the list goes on and on..... Roughly 9,000 healthcare workers have been infected and fallen ill...some have died. So for the general public who is so pro-reopen the economy and return to â€œnormalâ€ ASAP this virus will surge out of control! There wonâ€™t be enough hospital beds or people to take care of you! Let it sink in!

caption:
I thought I would get so much more accomplished now that I have the time.  I would return all the comments, catch up on all the posts, and watch all the stories.  I would create all the content, figure out the Pinterest/Facebook/IG balance, all while creating a home where you could finally see the bottom of the laundry basket.  I thought wrong.  Donâ€™t get it twisted.  I have been living my best life.  I have created plenty of beautiful photos and videos.  I have found all the free resources. I have done all the arts and crafts my crafty loving self can handle.
***
And Iâ€™ve accepted that what Iâ€™ve done is completely acceptable.  I did what I wanted to do... our one better, what I was called to do.  I needed to see that what I was TRYING to do was not worth doing.  It was not worth the time, energy or headache...who knew?  Take some inventory on all the things you thought you would do that you are beating yourself up for not doing right now.  Just because you see someone else doing it does not mean that YOU were supposed to be doing it.  Perhaps thatâ€™s not where you were called.  Perhaps it was not meant for YOU to do.  Make sure that what you are doing right now is in direct alignment with your purpose. #blessedmom #thelife
***

Two totally separate acts of kindness, on the same day, and it was just what I needed. caption:
Guys! I finally finished the pieces you have been seeing in my stories! All three of these are for the @amplifierart contest! I really wanted to enter this and Iâ€™m so glad that I found amplifier because you know mixing art with activism is kinda my thaaaang. I love that they are awarding artists for making art to spread the word about staying home, staying safe, staying sane and helping out our health professionals. I would GREATLY appreciate if you could vote for my pieces! You can head to my story and swipe up, or click the link in the bio of @amplifierart. Now about the pieces! The first piece is all about staying home and supporting each other. Everyone is saying â€œIâ€™m not gonna die from it so why should I stay home?!â€ You should stay home to help the WORLD not just yourself. If we want things to â€œget back to normalâ€ we have to come together, and all do our part. Staying home isnâ€™t just to protect you, itâ€™s to protect other peopleâ€™s health, the economy, small businesses.. itâ€™s not worth it to not listen. Stay in your bubble and call a friend! Not on a tin phone but you know what I mean hah. Piece two is all about staying sane and body positive during this time. I created this illustration of @bodyposipanda a while ago, and I wanted to refresh it by attaching a quote that is more relevant to today. When I saw this quote on her Instagram I knew it was perfect for this! Itâ€™s okay if you gain weight during this. You do not need to participate in workout challenges or diets. Itâ€™s okay if snacks are what is keeping you sane right now. Youâ€™re still amazing and beautiful! Eat whatever tf you want! The third piece is all about protecting our elders. In Asian countries they were able to get over this much faster... why?? Because they RESPECT their elders and want to keep them safe, so they stay inside. We need to treat them with that same respect! The first piece took almost 30 hours, more than Iâ€™ve spent on something in a long long time. Itâ€™s available in my shop as a poster and the lettering is on a tee! I hope you guys love it! .
.

caption:
How to Grow Mushrooms at Home for Mushroom Stir Fry with peas & onion (Sedapnya!) or Nasi Goreng with Cendawan, Pastas, Appetizers, and More.

But mushroom kan kulat (fungus)? Can grow at home meh.
Okay, there's no need to be in the dark about growing mushrooms. These tasty foods are extremely healthy: they're fat-free, low in calories, and filled with antioxidants, vitamins, and other nutrients, and they can even help keep our brain healthy too! This one I like, Woott wootttâ€¦

Senang je sebenarnya nak grow mushroom at home, the main keys to growing mushrooms at home are establishing the right growing conditions.  Mushrooms grow from spores (not seeds okay) that are so tiny you can't see individual spores with the naked eye. Mushrooms like dark, cool, and humid growing environments. When growing mushrooms at home, a place like a basement is ideal, but a spot under the sink could also work. 
Then how to get the spores lah? I will share that later in my next post. Till then, enjoy this Mushroom Stir Fry, maybe some idea for lunch later.

Confession time....just because Iâ€™m a licensed esthetician, that doesnâ€™t mean I always treat my skin right ğŸ˜¬ .
For example, my worst bad habit is picking. Iâ€™m a picker...I get a small pimple and I pick until itâ€™s a monster. THIS IS HORRIBLE FOR SKIN! One...it creates an environment for possible infection because Iâ€™ve created an open wound, it can cause a scar, and it can just end up causing more breakouts. .
So, how do I redeem myself and work on breaking this bad habit? I have a few tricks. â¬‡ï¸ 1ï¸âƒ£ First, I keep my nails really short! Canâ€™t pick if I donâ€™t have the tools right?! Plus, you can harbor a lot of nasty stuff under your nails. So, keeping nails short and clean is a great start. 
2ï¸âƒ£ Second, if I see a pimple I start take action right away. I apply a salicylic acid rich treatment to start working towards drying it out. A mask is a great way to stop them in their tracks. I apply the mask just to the pimple spot, it keeps me from touching it PLUS works itâ€™s magic. Sleep in it overnight, and you should see a major difference in the morning. A new thing is pimple patches. I havenâ€™t tried these yet, but itâ€™s on my to-do list. 
3ï¸âƒ£ The last thing I do is just try to stop breakouts before they even start. If there is nothing to pick, I canâ€™t be tempted. However, sometimes this is impossible, especially around my monthly cycle. When hormones get out of wack they trigger that annoying breakout, but keeping up with a daily skin care routine can greatly decrease the severity & longevity of that breakout. .

caption:
Downward dog is a pose that is done so often that it's sometimes perceived as an easy pose... it's not. It's actually quite complex. Like every pose, there is always more to work on in downward dog. When I first started, I had a huge backbend in the pose, so I worked on engaging my core until my back was straight. A huge tendency for soooo many people is rounding in the lumbar spine in downward dog. So next I worked on making sure that didn't happen for me. Next I made sure I wasn't hyper extending my knees. Then I worked on bringing my weight up and back rather than down into my hands. Currently I'm working on the muscle engagement and alignment of my hands. Once that is muscle memory, I'm sure there will be more to work on, forever. So if you think you've mastered downward dog, think again and search for the progression ğŸ˜ŠğŸ‘

caption:
Did you know stress can affect your skin?  With life today stress is pretty high for most people. .
Stress can cause more acne and breakouts.  Like we didn't have enough to worry about, right?
.
Hormonal changes and changes in diet can all be contributing factors.  Acne also doesn't happen overnight.  It takes week to see what is lurking beneath the surface. .
Hormonal fluctuations can increase cortisol levels. This then causes our skin to produce more oil which can lead to increases irritation, inflammation in the skin and acne. .
With lots of us at home and having kids at home with us means more junk food at home.  Eating high starchy, high sugary and non-fat foods increase glucose levels.  The response is our body creates more insulin which, bring our blood sugar down and increases oil produced by our glands.
.
WHAT'S THE SOLUTION?
.
Commit to a daily skin care routine and STICK TO IT!! .
Add a sulfur based mask 2-3 times a week to your weekly skin care regimen to get the acne under control faster. .
If dryness starts to occur from using your acne fighting products more simply add a hydrating serum and give your dehydrated skin some relief. .
Another important tip! KEEP YOUR HANDS AWAY FROM YOUR FACE!!! Yes, I'm talking to you.  Not only is it a good habit to keep from getting sick but your skin will also thank you. 
Need help finding the right skin care regimen for your skin?  I would love to help be your guide.

President Klaus Iohannis issued the decree of 30-day extension of the state of emergency and says we are struggling with an epidemic that is extremely difficult to control.

The Minister of Internal Affairs Marcel Vela announced the conclusion of an agreement between the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Romanian Patriarchate for sharing of the Resurrection Light and the Passover. Prescriptions will be distributed on Friday and Saturday in all parishes, in areas specially arranged outside the place of worship, and the observance of the distance measures will be ensured by the employees of the parishes and volunteers. The police forces coordinated by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs will assist the BOR with the sharing of the Holy Light on Saturday, starting at 8 pm.

7,216 cases of people with coronavirus have been confirmed since the beginning of the epidemic in Romania until today at 21.02 GMT, of which 1,217 are cured. 372 deaths were announced until 9.02 pm. #worldometersinfo 
Monica Anisie, Minister of Education and Research, approved the modification of the programs for the National Assessment and Bachelor's exams - they will no longer include the subject from the second semester. The ministry will also publish new training tests on April 22.

The National Directorate of Forests - Romsilva announced yesterday that it had seized 841,18 cubic meters of wood since the state of emergency was declared. Earlier in the month, environmental activists warned that illegal deforestation had multiplied and demanded that all deforestation be stopped. 
___
Amongst the #goodnews: @code4romania has launched the #RoHelp platform, where the NGOs looking for decreasing the COVID-19 crisis can collect resources to continue their projects. The organizations explain their needs and the citizens can donate for the projects they want to support.

The world's richest countries agreed on Wednesday, 15 April to freeze poor nations' debt obligations, shortly after nearly 20 European and African leaders made a joint appeal for a massive international effort to boost Africa's coronavirus response, saying that â€œonly a global victory that fully includes Africa can bring this pandemic to an end.â€ Finance ministers of the G-20 group of major economies, which includes the US, China, India and others, said they will immediately put on hold poor countries' obligations to service debt they owe.

The statement issued after a video conference put to rest concerns that China would block such a measure, which is aimed at helping the poorest nations focus their spending on healthcare and assistance to vulnerable people to contain the outbreak and its fallout.

Source: thequint

caption:
During the last 48 hours, I spent my time with my in-laws making 180 masks ğŸ˜· for my motherâ€™s assisted living community in Oregon. â €
â €
Even if we donâ€™t have money to give, we all have something to offer during this time. It can be using your time to help make masks. It can look like a phone call to someone feeling lonely in isolation. It can look like picking up groceries for your immune suppressed neighbor. â €
â €
Itâ€™s sometimes really hard to put ourselves in the shoes of others, but now I think we should all try a little harder. During COVID, Iâ€™ve often only considered those in my shoesâ€”people currently out of work. But I havenâ€™t taken much time to put myself in the shoes of others until now. â €
â €
The elderly are isolated more than normal. Theyâ€™re unable to fiend for themselves in so many aspects of life. They are confused. They are upset. They are at risk. And to be honest, theyâ€™re dying at a more rapid rate than anyone else.â €
â €
My grandmother has dementia and she gets very frustrated with change... which in turn deteriorates her memory further. This situation is a big change for many of us, but can you imagine this change for the elderly who may not understand or comprehend or be able to remember whatâ€™s happening? It breaks my heart. â €
â €
If you can do anything during this time, offer anything to someone in need, maybe make a phone call, send a card or mail a letter to someone who needs a little bit of love right now. Itâ€™s the least we can give to the rest of the world who is suffering right along with us. â €
â €

caption:
WICHITA, Kan. (KAKE) - More than 19,000 small Kansas businesses have won some $3.7 billion in federal aid through a loan program designed to help them keep employees working through the pandemic.  But some of those businesses say confusion over requirements could end up hurting them more than the loans might help.â €
â €
Mike Mathia was excited when Congress approved the Paycheck Protection Program (PPP), a loan for businesses with 500 or fewer employees, run by the Small Business Administration.  That excitement died when his bank told Mathia he couldnâ€™t include his subcontractors on the application as employees.â €
â €
â€œOur loan funds were cut by 75% with this change,â€ he said.â €
â €
Not only did it cut the amount his company was eligible for, he says it could permanently cost him the work of those independent contractors once the crisis is over.â €
â €
â€œIf start-ups and small businesses don't have the funding or the capital to preserve their services, these contractors are saying, â€˜What do I do long-term for both work and income?â€™â€ Mathia explained. â €
â €
Mathia says heâ€™s reached out to his congressman and senators. â €
â €
Congressman Ron Estesâ€™ office told KAKE News itâ€™s looking into Mathiaâ€™s concerns, but the congressman believed the program already allowed businesses to claim subcontractors as employees.â €
â €
Whether the problem is confusion at the bank over the rules of a new program or an unconsidered side effect, Mathia says he believes the speed at which the PPP rolled out may be the real culprit.â €
â €

â €

â €
â€œIâ€™ve been stuck in the house playing video games," said Epke. "So itâ€™s nice to be able to actually get outside and do something physical and a little bit athletic."â €

caption:
An emailÂ to parents from a wise principal:

What If???? Many people are concerned about students falling behind because of this. Yes, they may fall behind when it comes to classroom education... But what if... What if instead of falling â€œbehind", this group of kids are ADVANCED because of this? Hear me out... What if they have more empathy, they enjoy family connection, they can be more creative and entertain themselves, they love to read, they love to express themselves in writing.

What if they enjoy the simple things, like their own backyard and sitting near a window in the quiet.

What if they notice the birds and the dates the different flowers emerge, and the calming renewal of a gentle rain shower?

What if this generation are the ones to learn to cook, organize their space, do their laundry, and keep a well run home? 
What if they learn to stretch a dollar and to live with less?

What if they learn to plan shopping trips and meals at home.

What if they learn the value of eating together as a family and finding the good to share in the small delights of the everyday?

What if they are the ones to place great value on our teachers and educational professionals, librarians, public servants and the previously invisible essential support workers like truck drivers, grocers, cashiers, custodians, logistics, and health care workers and their supporting staff, just to name a few of the millions taking care of us right now while we are sheltered in place?

What if among these children, a great leader emerges who had the benefit of a slower pace and a simpler life to truly learn what really matters in this life?

What if they are AHEAD? 
To sum it up for you friends: The kids are alright!

NEWS INDIA BREAKING: At a time governments and health experts around the world are stressing on social distancing to contain the spread of coronavirus, a photo of Muslims offering namaaz in groups on rooftops has gone viral on social media.

Many on social media thought the picture to be from India. The photo is going viral on Twitter and Facebook with the caption, â€œWhen about them, Narendra Modi ji? They least care for your request, appeal, etc. Will they also face the law, since they donâ€™t seem to obey the law atleast willinglyâ€. The archived version of the post can be seen here.India Today Anti Fake News War Room (AFWA) has found the claim along with the photo to be false. This photo of namaaz in groups is from Kuwait. However, similar incidents have been reported in India too. 
An Arabic website â€œHowiyaPressâ€ had used this picture in an article dated April 13, 2020. The translation of this article says that the photo was taken in a town called Jleeb Al-Shuyoukh in Kuwait.

Source: India Today

caption:
NEWS INDIA BREAKING: The Bengal government has finally formulated a standard operating procedure (SOP) to stop mixing of Covid-19 suspects with non-Covid patients in state-run hospitals. This came after a few state-run and private hospitals got hit when some patients were detected with coronavirus while they were being treated in general wards along with other patients.

Various wards in state-run and private hospitals had to be closed down for sanitization, dozens of doctors and nurses had to be sent in quarantine and samples of many non-Covid patients had to be tested because they had all come in close contact with Covid-19 suspects. The suspects ultimately turned out to be coronavirus patients. â€œThe SOP was formulated to stop mixing of Covid suspects with others. The SOP contains detailed guidelines on how Covid-19 suspects should be handled at the emergency sections and in other wards of hospitals. It also includes guidelines on how to handle relatives of such patients and suspects,â€ said a top official of the state health department. The SOP was issued on Tuesday.

On April 12, a woman was detected with Covid-19 soon after giving birth at the Calcutta Medical College and Hospital. The woman and her newborn had to be separated, the labour and surgery room had to be closed down for two days for sanitization and other patients in adjacent beds also had to be tested. Doctorsâ€™ samples had to be tested and they were asked to go in quarantine.

Source: Hindustan Times

US President Donald Trump has announced that heâ€™ll be cutting funding to the World Health Organization (WHO) over its handling of the pandemic of the novel coronavirus. "I am directing my administration to halt funding while a review is conducted to assess the World Health Organization's role in severely mismanaging and covering up the spread of the coronavirus," the US President said during a news conference at the White House.

The US is the biggest contributor to the WHO budget, along with the United Nations, Republic of Korea, Australia, and the Gates Foundation falling in the top 5. 
He has accused the WHO of having 'criticised' the decision to place travel restrictions on travel from China in late January -- when the infection had already begun to spread -- and of being biased towards China more generally.

The WHO is yet to directly respond but UN Secretary-General AntÃ³nio Guterres said it was 'not the time' to cut funds to the WHO and that the international community should be uniting 'in solidarity to stop this virus'.

Update 34......its a big day tomorrow.

It's going to be a big one tomorrow.Â  Not only is the Queen of Denmark turning the ripe old age of 80 (albeit a spring chicken compared to the Queen of England at 93), but BBB also returns to Kindergarten (orÂ bÃ¸rnehaveÂ as its known in Danish). There's been a bit of nervousness all around, but the Danish Prime Minister is just about as popular as the New Zealand Prime Minister and slowly the masses are feeling okay about it. Plus the concept of trust is a big Danish value (I had to study about it for 2 weeks at language school), which is helping people accept we must move forward even if its a bit bloody scary.

Denmark is the first European country to re-open schools (for 1-11-year-olds). And there's a new & lengthy list of social distancing requirements by the Government for all the schools which include havingÂ 4m2 per child and that they must play with the same small groups of 3-5 mainly outside as well as having to sit two metres apart at tables. And most horrifying to me is that now I have to make her lunch EVERY day.Â  Back in the old days, we were spoilt with the Kindergarten providing lunch.

Today we had a Kiwi ham, cheese and pineapple toastie (that's a toasted sandwich), on 'white bread' which really isn't white bread, its multigrain bread, but that's classified as white in Denmark where brown only means the darkest, heaviest rye bread you can imagine.Â  BBB was thrilled with lunch and The Dane was horrified, so he's probably quite looking forward to tomorrow I suspect.

And as for me?Â  I'm gonna miss my 'Smoko' buddy but also quietlly going to enjoy being able to get shit done.

caption:
In the case of huge gathering of migrant laborers at Mumbai's Bandra railway station, the police has arrested a person named Vinay Dubey.  Vinay Dubey was detained by Navi Mumbai Police and handed over to Mumbai Police.  Amid the lockdown, Vinay Dubey is accused of misleading the crowd.

Vinay Dubey was running the campaign 'Let's go home'. In his post shared on Facebook, he had said that the team is in Bandra.  In this case, the police has registered an FIR against one thousand people. A case has been registered against Dubey under sections 117, 153A, 188, 269, 270, 505 (2) of the IPC and section 3 of the Epidemic Act.

Let us know that on Tuesday, a huge crowd of migrant laborers gathered at Mumbai's Bandra railway station.  All these workers reached the station to go home.  The workers hoped that the lockdown would end.  The police had to lathicharge to remove them.  However, migrant laborers have now been removed from there.  Lockdown has been extended till May 3 across the country.

Home Minister Amit Shah expressed concern over the incident.  He said that this is not right in the midst of the ongoing fight against Corona.  In this regard, he spoke to CM Uddhav Thackeray over phone.  At the same time, Uddhav Thackeray said that the government will arrange these workers.  They do not have to worry.

Here, Aditya Thackeray, Minister in Maharashtra Government tweeted on this whole incident and targeted the Central Government.  He said that some workers had rioted in Surat recently.  The central government could not take a decision to take them home.  Aditya Thackeray said that migrant laborers do not want food and shelter, they want to go home.

ğŸ“ºTurn off the tv. Personally I would recommend not having a tv in your sleeping space. I realize not everyone has that option as their room may be all their space. If you need to sleep with noise, try a noise machine, or even a fan on low gives off a white noise effect.
.
ğŸƒâ€â™€ï¸Exercise eariler in the day. In general we should be trying to move our bodies for at least 30 mins a day. Just not right before you go to sleep as exercise gets your heart pumping, which gets your blood circulatung, and energy flowing, to which you are then trying to calm your body for sleep.
.
ğŸ´Eating properly, as best you can. The reality is not everyone can afford to eat how they want, when they have a whole family to feed and buying bulk to cheaper than a little bundle of nutritional apples.
.
ğŸ§–â€â™€ï¸Diffusing essential oils such as lavender.
.

caption:
It is now more important than ever to be mindful with our bodies and to exercise beneficial practices for the mind and soul. Find a daily meditation ritual that helps with focus, anxiety, or gratitude. Engage in meditations focused around the positive aspects of your current life. Our mind is a muscle that needs to be exercised and in uncertain and anxiety-ridden times, meditation can help us re-evaluate where we stand and realign our energy. It's easy to focus on the negative things occuring around us, that's how the brain works - it looks for problems. It's time to be laser focused, if a negative thought pattern comes up, just observe it without attaching to it and let it pass. Avoid going down the rabbit hole and exercise discipline by switching to a more favorable thought that leaves you feeling good. Mental discipline is important, meditate, use mantras and affirmations. 
And be sure to join Dr. Isabel for an Instagram live with Dr. Eric Roy PHD, founder of @hydroviv_h2o at 2 PM!

The novelÂ coronavirusÂ kills by inflaming and clogging the tiny air sacs in the lungs. But clinicians around the world are seeing evidence that suggests the virus also may be causing heart inflammation, acute kidney disease, neurological malfunction, blood clots, intestinal damage and liver problems. That development has complicated treatment for the most severe cases of covid-19, the illness caused by the virus, and makes the course of recovery less certain, medical professionals say. Early data that shows 14Â to 30Â percent of intensive-care patients in New York and Wuhan, China â€” birthplace of the pandemic â€” have lost kidney function and require dialysis, or its in-hospital cousin, continuous renal replacement therapy.

caption:
How to use #arogya Setu app and find out if you have Corona symptoms.
1.After you've run the app, allow it to access your device's location, as prompted.
2. You'll get an OTP, enter it and you are on.
3. Choose your gender from the options given.
4. Enter your full name, then age, and then profession, as asked.
5. You'll be asked about your foreign travel history in last 30 days. Give the appropriate answer. Your foreign travel history, if any, will be matched with that of those who've tested positive, with the help of ICMR database.

Then, the app asks you whether or not you are ready to volunteer in the times of need. Assuming you answer Yes, a 20-second assessment test starts.

After you have installed Aarogya Setu in your phone, it will detect other nearby smartphones that also have the app installed. It can then figure out the risk of infection based on sophisticated parameters if any of these contacts is tested positive.

The basis of this calculation â€” which is done using Bluetooth, algorithms and artificial intelligence â€” is the smartphone user's interaction with others.
if you didn't install the app,first install the app ASAP.

Pada 10 April lalu, warga di South Windsor, Amerika membuat kejutan untuk seorang dokter muslim Dr. Saud Anwar dengan konvoi mobil ke rumahnya, utk menunjukkan rasa terima kasih mereka atas pekerjaan yang beliau lakukan di garis depan penanganan virus corona.â£
.â£
Dan lebih dari itu beliau berhasil membuat alat pengaturan Ventilator (alat bantu pernafasan) yang dapat disalurkan untuk 7 orang pasien sekali pasang. â£
=ventilator dipasang di ruang ICU pada pasien gagal nafas, biasanya 1 ventilator utk 1 pasien saja=â£
.â£
â£
Ini benar-benar penemuan yang sangat dibutuhkan ditengah kelangkaan ventilator akibat banyaknya jumlah yang terinfeksi covid-19.â£
.â£
â£
Warga di South Windsor melakukan pawai "pahlawan tanpa tanda jasa" untuk menghormati Dr Saud Anwar. Mereka menempelkan poster di kendaraan mereka dengan berbagai tulisan seperti 'Dr Saud Anwar Kepahlawanan Anda menginspirasi kami!' 'Terima kasih untuk kepahlawanan Anda' dll (â€˜Dr Saud Anwarâ€™ â€˜Your heroism inspires us!â€™ â€˜thank youâ€™ â€˜thank you for your heroismâ€™ etc.)â£
.â£
â£
Dr Saud menjawab : â€œTerima kasih atas semua orang yang datang hari ini untuk mengejutkan saya. Saya benar-benar kewalahan dengan CINTA yang Anda semua tunjukkan. Saya merasa mendapat barokah untuk menjadi bagian dari komunitas ini dan juga bekerja dengan kelompok pekerja kesehatan terbaik yang saya cintai dan hormati.â€â£
